==English==

===Etymology===
{{etyl|enm|en}} {{term/t|enm|forgiven||to forgive}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term/t|ang|forġiefan||to forgive, give up, provide}}, corresponding to {{prefix|for|give}}. Cognate with {{etyl|nl|-}} {{term|vergeven|lang=nl}}, {{etyl|de|-}} {{term|vergeben|lang=de}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{enPR|fər-gĭv', fôr-gĭv'}}, {{IPA|/fə(r)ˈɡɪv/|/fɔː(r)ˈɡɪv/}}
* {{audio|en-us-forgive.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{rhymes|ɪv}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|forgives|forgiving|forgave|forgiven}}

# {{context|transitive|lang=en}} To [[pardon]], to waive any negative feeling or desire for punishment.
#: ''Only the brave know how to '''forgive'''...A coward never '''forgave'''; it is not in his nature.'' - [[q: Laurence Sterne| Laurence Sterne]]
# {{context|intransitive|lang=en}} To [[accord]] [[forgiveness]].

